The issue with your code is that you are not displaying the progress dialog in the `onPreExecute()` method of your `AsyncTask`. To fix this, you can add a `ProgressDialog` to your `DownloadFileFromURL` class and show it in the `onPreExecute()` method. Here's an updated version of your code:
```java
class DownloadFileFromURL extends AsyncTask<String, String, String> {
    private ProgressDialog progressDialog;

    @Override
    protected void onPreExecute() {
        super.onPreExecute();
        progressDialog = new ProgressDialog(context);
        progressDialog.setMessage("Downloading...");
        progressDialog.show();
    }

    @Override
    protected String doInBackground(String... f_url) {
        // ...
    }

    @Override
    protected void onPostExecute(String file_url) {
        super.onPostExecute(file_url);
        progressDialog.dismiss();
    }
}
```
In this updated code, we create a `ProgressDialog` object in the `onPreExecute()` method and show it using the `show()` method. In the `onPostExecute()` method, we dismiss the progress dialog using the `dismiss()` method.
